ozens of key topics, including eggs, caterpillars, and chrysalids; flight, feeding, courtship, and mating; migration and hibernation; concealment, mimicry, and predators; habitat loss and fragmentation, climate change, and pesticides; and farming and gardening to support and attract butterflies.With its stunning illustrations and clear, up-to-date, and authoritative text, The Lives of Butterflies will appeal to a wide range of butterfly and nature lovers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aButterfliesvIdentification. 0aButterfliesxLife cycles. 0aButterflies. 7aNATURE / Butterflies & Moths.2bisacsh1 aLohman, David J., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishz978311131921608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023z9783111318615oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074974808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook packagez978311123611740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691241128?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691241128423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780691241128/original  a978-3-11-074974-8  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-123611-7  UIUC Life Sciences 2023 eBook packageb2023  a978-3-11-131921-6  EBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEB